        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>[Down]</placeName>
                    <date>May 18<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>My health has suddenly quite failed. I leave home tomorrow for <hi rend="underline">one</hi> weeks rest.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I have written to M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Clowes to say that I shall be ready to begin correcting on 27<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>Yours very sincerely | C. Darwin Down Bromley Kent</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Dated by the relationship to the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2463.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. D. Hooker, 18 [May 1859]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2463.xml" resp="#mjhawkins" cert="high">letter to J. D. Hooker   18 [May 1859]</ref>. CD visited Moor Park hydropathic establishment from 21 to 28 May 1859 (‘Journal’; Appendix II).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_978.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Clowes</ref> was Murray’s usual printer. CD began reading proof-sheets on 25 May (‘Journal’; Appendix II).</note>
        </div>        
            
